;; ESH-0095 minimal repro (found by the AD composition oracle, P3).
;; hessian with a TENSOR point (literal #(...) or (tensor ...)) SIGSEGVs.
;; The same function with a (vector ...) point works and returns the
;; correct hessian. laplacian has the same failure (see the sibling
;; repro file); all FIRST-order ops (gradient/jacobian/divergence/curl)
;; accept tensor points fine — only the second-order ops crash.
;;
;; Run: build/eshkol-run -r tests/ad_oracle/found/esh0095_hessian_tensor_point_sigsegv.esk
;; Expected: #((4 2) (2 0)) twice. Actual: first display OK, then SIGSEGV.
(display (hessian (lambda (v) (* (vref v 0) (vref v 0) (vref v 1))) (vector 1.0 2.0)))
(newline)
(display (hessian (lambda (v) (* (vref v 0) (vref v 0) (vref v 1))) (tensor 1.0 2.0)))
(newline)
